  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large paella pan over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the diced onion and cook until translucent, about 3-4 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional minute.",
    "Add the arborio rice and cook for 1-2 minutes, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the canned kidney beans, artichoke hearts, smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper. Stir to combine.",
    "Add the lemon juice and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20-25 minutes.",
    "Remove the lid and cook for an additional 5-10 minutes, or until the rice is tender and the liquid has been absorbed.",
    "Garnish with chopped fresh parsley and serve immediately."
